==English==

===Etymology===
Hindi from Sanskrit ''namaskāra'', from ''namas'': "to bow", "[[obeisance]]" and ''kāra'': "action".

===Noun===
'''namaskar''' (countable)
# ''(Indian English)'' The movement used when [[greet]]ing someone in which you put your hands together and then [[bow]] slightly.

